Based on my comprehensive research, here is a complete summary of ExtendScript and CEP for Adobe Premiere Pro:

---

## 1. Does ExtendScript Provide Razor Tool or Clip Splitting Functionality?

**No, there is no direct "cut" or "razor" function in the official ExtendScript API.**

However, there are two approaches:

### Option A: QE DOM Razor Method (Unsupported/Unofficial)
```javascript
// Enable Quality Engineering library (unsupported API)
app.enableQE();

// Get the active QE sequence
var sqe = qe.project.getActiveSequence();

// Get player time in timecode format "00:00:03:38"
var playerTime = sqe.CTI.timecode;

// Razor on a specific track
sqe.getVideoTrackAt(0).razor(playerTime);

// Or razor on all tracks
sqe.razor(playerTime);
```

**Warning**: The QE DOM is undocumented and unsupported by Adobe. It was built for internal testing and may break in future versions.

### Option B: Manual Workaround Using TrackItem Properties
```javascript
// Adjust the existing clip's end point, then insert a new clip
// for the remaining portion

var clip = app.project.activeSequence.videoTracks[0].clips[0];
var splitTime = 5.0; // seconds

// Store original values
var originalOutPoint = clip.outPoint.seconds;
var originalEnd = clip.end.seconds;

// Shorten the first clip
var newEnd = clip.end;
newEnd.seconds = splitTime;
clip.end = newEnd;

// Then insert the remaining portion as a new clip
// (requires the source projectItem and calculating new in/out points)
```

---

## 2. Timeline Editing APIs Available in ExtendScript for Premiere Pro

### Sequence Object Methods
| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `insertClip(projectItem, time, vTrackIndex, aTrackIndex)` | Inserts clip, shifts existing clips |
| `overwriteClip(projectItem, time, vTrackIndex, aTrackIndex)` | Inserts clip, overwrites existing content |
| `getSelection()` | Returns array of selected TrackItem objects |
| `linkSelection()` / `unlinkSelection()` | Link/unlink selected clips |
| `createSubsequence()` | Creates subsequence from in to out point |
| `getPlayerPosition()` | Gets CTI position in ticks |
| `setPlayerPosition(time)` | Moves playhead |
| `setInPoint(time)` / `setOutPoint(time)` | Sets sequence in/out points |
| `performSceneEditDetectionOnSelection()` | Detects scene cuts |

### Track Object Properties
- `app.project.activeSequence.videoTracks` - TrackCollection of video tracks
- `app.project.activeSequence.audioTracks` - TrackCollection of audio tracks
- Each track has a `clips` property (TrackItemCollection)

### TrackItem Properties (Read/Write)
| Property | Type | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| `inPoint` | Time | Source in point (relative to source start) |
| `outPoint` | Time | Source out point (relative to source start) |
| `start` | Time | Timeline start position |
| `end` | Time | Timeline end position |
| `name` | String | Clip name |
| `projectItem` | ProjectItem | Reference to source media |

---

## 3. Using app.project.activeSequence for Clip Manipulation

### Basic Access Pattern
```javascript
// Get active sequence
var seq = app.project.activeSequence;

// Access video tracks
var videoTrack = seq.videoTracks[0];

// Iterate through clips on track
for (var i = 0; i < videoTrack.clips.numItems; i++) {
    var clip = videoTrack.clips[i];
    $.writeln("Clip: " + clip.name);
    $.writeln("  Start: " + clip.start.seconds);
    $.writeln("  End: " + clip.end.seconds);
    $.writeln("  InPoint: " + clip.inPoint.seconds);
    $.writeln("  OutPoint: " + clip.outPoint.seconds);
}

// Get selected clips
var selection = seq.getSelection();
for (var j = 0; j < selection.length; j++) {
    $.writeln("Selected: " + selection[j].name);
}

// Get current playhead position
var playerPos = seq.getPlayerPosition();
var playerSeconds = playerPos.seconds;
```

### Inserting Clips
```javascript
var projectItem = app.project.rootItem.children[0]; // First item in project
var insertTime = 10.0; // seconds
var videoTrackIndex = 0;
var audioTrackIndex = 0;

// Insert (shifts existing clips)
seq.insertClip(projectItem, insertTime, videoTrackIndex, audioTrackIndex);

// Or overwrite (replaces existing content)
seq.overwriteClip(projectItem, insertTime, videoTrackIndex, audioTrackIndex);
```

### Modifying Clip Duration
```javascript
var clip = seq.videoTracks[0].clips[0];

// Extend clip by 3 seconds
var newEnd = clip.end;
newEnd.seconds = newEnd.seconds + 3;
clip.end = newEnd;
```

---

## 4. Is CEP Still Supported in Premiere Pro 2024/2025?

**Yes, CEP is still fully supported.**

| Version | Status |
|---------|--------|
| **CEP 12** | Shipped with Premiere Pro 25.0 (2024/2025) |
| **CEP Future** | CEP 12 is the last major update; security patches will continue |
| **ExtendScript** | Supported through at least **September 2026** |
| **Deprecation** | No retirement schedule announced; Adobe commits to "significant overlap period" before any deprecation |

**Key Points**:
- CEP extensibility is "very definitely still supported"
- Adobe will provide 1.5-2 years of overlap when transitioning (based on Flex-to-CEP precedent)
- For production panels shipping soon, **CEP remains recommended**

---

## 5. Differences Between CEP and UXP for Premiere Pro

| Feature | CEP (Current) | UXP (Beta/Future) |
|---------|---------------|-------------------|
| **Status** | Production-ready, stable | Public beta (Dec 2024) |
| **Engine** | Chromium Embedded Framework | Adobe's lightweight JS engine |
| **Performance** | Higher memory usage | Faster load, lower memory |
| **ExtendScript** | Full access via evalScript() | Not available |
| **API Completeness** | Full DOM + QE DOM | Limited, growing |
| **Timeline Editing** | Supported (via ExtendScript) | Limited/incomplete |
| **Razor/Split** | Via QE DOM (unsupported) | Not yet available |
| **Async Model** | Synchronous (blocks UI) | Asynchronous (non-blocking) |
| **Support Timeline** | Through Sept 2026+ | Full release expected 2025 |

### UXP Current Limitations
- No razor tool or clip splitting API
- Cannot move clips between tracks
- Many timeline editing APIs not yet implemented
- Still in beta with limited documentation

### Recommendation
- **For production now**: Use CEP + ExtendScript
- **For future-proofing**: Start testing UXP, provide feedback to Adobe
- **For timeline manipulation**: CEP + ExtendScript (with QE DOM if needed)

